 Return Values :

A function can return a value back to the code that called it.

When a function reaches a return statement, the function stops executing.The value after the return keyword is sent back to the caller.

function add(a, b) {
 return a + b;
}

let result = add(5, 3);
console.log(result); 

Outpu : 8

